      "source": [
        "def get_file_size(path):\n",
        "    return os.path.getsize(path) if os.path.isfile(path) else 0\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "317c7006-06d9-401a-b524-f978dd185bbf",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### 📦 Compute Combined File Sizes for Source–Mutant Pairs\n",
        "\n",
        "We now construct a mapping called `size_map` that records the combined size (in bytes) of each source–mutant file pair.\n",
        "\n",
        "#### Logic:\n",
        "- Iterate over each project in `files_map`.\n",
        "- For every mutant file associated with the project:\n",
        "  - Use `get_file_size()` to get the size of both the source file and the mutant file.\n",
        "  - Sum the sizes to get the total file size for that pair.\n",
        "  - Use the last two parts of the mutant path (i.e., `mutant_version/filename`) as the key for easy identification.\n",
        "\n",
        "#### Resulting Structure:\n",
        "```python\n",
        "size_map = {\n",
        "    \"mutant_version/filename\": (\n",
        "        \"path/to/source/file\",\n",
        "        \"path/to/mutant/file\",\n",
        "        combined_file_size_in_bytes\n",
        "    ),\n",
        "    ...\n",
        "}\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 10,
      "id": "88c1abbe",
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [
        {
          "data": {
            "text/plain": [
              "dict_keys(['elevator', 'Problem2', 'Problem3', 'nsichneu', 'Problem1', 'merge2BSTree', 'quicksort', 'cfg_test', 'nextDate1', 'adpcm'])"
            ]
          },
          "execution_count": 10,
          "metadata": {},
          "output_type": "execute_result"
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "files_map.keys()\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 11,
      "id": "3496e9e4-1c28-41fc-9976-14e0ea8438e8",
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "size_map = {}\n",
        "for key in files_map:\n",
        "    file_tuple = files_map[key]\n",
        "    for mutant in file_tuple[1]:\n",
        "        path_obj = Path(mutant)\n",
        "        key_str = '/'.join(path_obj.parts[-2:])\n",
        "        size_map.setdefault(key_str, (file_tuple[0], mutant, int(get_file_size(file_tuple[0]) + get_file_size(mutant))))"
      ]
    },
